channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Aligning Bag of Regions for Open-Vocabulary Object Detection
item.description: The embeddings of regions in a bag are treated as embeddings of words in a sentence, and they are sent to the text encoder of a VLM to obtain the bag-of-regions embedding, which is learned to be aligned to the corresponding features extracted by a frozen VLM.

item.title: Learning Topology-Specific Experts for Molecular Property Prediction
item.description: In this paper, motivated by this observation, we propose \proposed to leverage topology-specific prediction models (referred to as experts), each of which is responsible for each molecular group sharing similar topological semantics.

item.title: Multi-Feature Integration for Perception-Dependent Examination-Bias Estimation
item.description: Eliminating examination bias accurately is pivotal to apply click-through data to train an unbiased ranking model.

item.title: Quantifying Valence and Arousal in Text with Multilingual Pre-trained Transformers
item.description: The analysis of emotions expressed in text has numerous applications.

item.title: Internet Explorer: Targeted Representation Learning on the Open Web
item.description: Modern vision models typically rely on fine-tuning general-purpose models pre-trained on large, static datasets.

item.title: The Role of Pre-training Data in Transfer Learning
item.description: We investigate the impact of pre-training data distribution on the few-shot and full fine-tuning performance using 3 pre-training methods (supervised, contrastive language-image and image-image), 7 pre-training datasets, and 9 downstream datasets.

item.title: FedCLIP: Fast Generalization and Personalization for CLIP in Federated Learning
item.description: Concretely, we design an attention-based adapter for the large model, CLIP, and the rest operations merely depend on adapters.

item.title: Causal isotonic calibration for heterogeneous treatment effects
item.description: We propose causal isotonic calibration, a novel nonparametric method for calibrating predictors of heterogeneous treatment effects.

item.title: The (Ab)use of Open Source Code to Train Large Language Models
item.description: In recent years, Large Language Models (LLMs) have gained significant popularity due to their ability to generate human-like text and their potential applications in various fields, such as Software Engineering.

item.description: Thus, model's comprehension ability towards real scenarios are hard to evaluate reasonably.

item.title: Neural Graph Revealers
item.description: Sparse graph recovery methods works well where the data follows their assumptions but often they are not designed for doing downstream probabilistic queries.

item.title: Extrapolated cross-validation for randomized ensembles
item.description: Our method builds on two main ingredients: two initial estimators for small ensemble sizes using out-of-bag errors and a novel risk extrapolation technique leveraging the structure of the prediction risk decomposition.

item.title: Systematic Rectification of Language Models via Dead-end Analysis
item.description: Other methods rely on rule-based or prompt-based token elimination, which are limited as they dismiss future tokens and the overall meaning of the complete discourse.

item.title: Inseq: An Interpretability Toolkit for Sequence Generation Models
item.description: Past work in natural language processing interpretability focused mainly on popular classification tasks while largely overlooking generation settings, partly due to a lack of dedicated tools.

item.title: Evaluating Robustness and Uncertainty of Graph Models Under Structural Distributional Shifts
item.description: To evaluate the performance of graph models, it is important to test them on diverse and meaningful distributional shifts.

item.title: Spatially-Adaptive Feature Modulation for Efficient Image Super-Resolution
item.description: Although numerous solutions have been proposed for image super-resolution, they are usually incompatible with low-power devices with many computational and memory constraints.

item.title: OccDepth: A Depth-Aware Method for 3D Semantic Scene Completion
item.description: 3D Semantic Scene Completion (SSC) can provide dense geometric and semantic scene representations, which can be applied in the field of autonomous driving and robotic systems.

item.title: IGB: Addressing The Gaps In Labeling, Features, Heterogeneity, and Size of Public Graph Datasets for Deep Learning Research
item.description: Most existing public datasets for GNNs are relatively small, which limits the ability of GNNs to generalize to unseen data.

item.title: Image to Sphere: Learning Equivariant Features for Efficient Pose Prediction
item.description: Predicting the pose of objects from a single image is an important but difficult computer vision problem.

item.title: Learning to Generalize towards Unseen Domains via a Content-Aware Style Invariant Framework for Disease Detection from Chest X-rays
item.description: Several methods have been proposed to address this domain shift, such as utilizing adversarial learning or multi-domain mixups to extract domain-invariant high-level features.

item.title: LLaMA: Open and Efficient Foundation Language Models
item.description: We introduce LLaMA, a collection of foundation language models ranging from 7B to 65B parameters.

item.title: kNN-BOX: A Unified Framework for Nearest Neighbor Generation
item.description: Augmenting the base neural model with a token-level symbolic datastore is a novel generation paradigm and has achieved promising results in machine translation (MT).

item.title: LODE: Locally Conditioned Eikonal Implicit Scene Completion from Sparse LiDAR
item.description: In this paper, we propose a novel Eikonal formulation that conditions the implicit representation on localized shape priors which function as dense boundary value constraints, and demonstrate it works on SemanticKITTI and SemanticPOSS.

item.title: Efficient Informed Proposals for Discrete Distributions via Newton's Series Approximation
item.description: Gradients have been exploited in proposal distributions to accelerate the convergence of Markov chain Monte Carlo algorithms on discrete distributions.

item.title: SpikeGPT: Generative Pre-trained Language Model with Spiking Neural Networks
item.description: Spiking neural networks (SNNs) have emerged as an energy-efficient approach to deep learning that leverage sparse and event-driven activations to reduce the computational overhead associated with model inference.

item.title: Learning to Super-Resolve Blurry Images with Events
item.description: Super-Resolution from a single motion Blurred image (SRB) is a severely ill-posed problem due to the joint degradation of motion blurs and low spatial resolution.

item.title: Self Correspondence Distillation for End-to-End Weakly-Supervised Semantic Segmentation
item.description: In addition, to further improve the segmentation accuracy, we design a Variation-aware Refine Module to enhance the local consistency of pseudo-labels by computing pixel-level variation.

item.title: Language Is Not All You Need: Aligning Perception with Language Models
item.description: A big convergence of language, multimodal perception, action, and world modeling is a key step toward artificial general intelligence.

item.title: Target-Aware Tracking with Long-term Context Attention
item.description: Most deep trackers still follow the guidance of the siamese paradigms and use a template that contains only the target without any contextual information, which makes it difficult for the tracker to cope with large appearance changes, rapid target movement, and attraction from similar objects.

item.title: GNNDelete: A General Strategy for Unlearning in Graph Neural Networks
item.description: Deleted Edge Consistency ensures that the influence of deleted elements is removed from both model weights and neighboring representations, while Neighborhood Influence guarantees that the remaining model knowledge is preserved after deletion.

item.title: Efficient fair PCA for fair representation learning
item.description: We revisit the problem of fair principal component analysis (PCA), where the goal is to learn the best low-rank linear approximation of the data that obfuscates demographic information.

item.title: Tailoring Language Generation Models under Total Variation Distance
item.description: The standard paradigm of neural language generation adopts maximum likelihood estimation (MLE) as the optimizing method.

item.title: MDF-Net: Multimodal Dual-Fusion Network for Abnormality Detection using CXR Images and Clinical Data
item.description: In this work, we propose a novel architecture consisting of two fusion methods that enable the model to simultaneously process patients' clinical data (structured data) and chest X-rays (image data).

item.title: Learning Input-agnostic Manipulation Directions in StyleGAN with Text Guidance
item.description: With the advantages of fast inference and human-friendly flexible manipulation, image-agnostic style manipulation via text guidance enables new applications that were not previously available.

item.title: Performance is not enough: a story of the Rashomon's quartet
item.description: But what if the second best model describes the data equally well but in a completely different way?

item.title: Learning Pairwise Interaction for Generalizable DeepFake Detection
item.description: We obtain 98. 48% BOSC accuracy on the FF++ dataset and 90. 87% BOSC accuracy on the CelebDF dataset suggesting a promising direction for generalization of DeepFake detection.

item.title: PDIWS: Thermal Imaging Dataset for Person Detection in Intrusion Warning Systems
item.description: In this paper, we present a synthetic thermal imaging dataset for Person Detection in Intrusion Warning Systems (PDIWS).

item.title: Closed-loop Error Correction Learning Accelerates Experimental Discovery of Thermoelectric Materials
item.description: The exploration of thermoelectric materials is challenging considering the large materials space, combined with added exponential degrees of freedom coming from doping and the diversity of synthetic pathways.

item.title: Kernel Conditional Moment Constraints for Confounding Robust Inference
item.description: It can be shown that our estimator contains the recently proposed sharp estimator by Dorn and Guo (2022) as a special case, and our method enables a novel extension of the classical marginal sensitivity model using f-divergence.

item.title: Cross-Lingual Question Answering over Knowledge Base as Reading Comprehension
item.description: We convert KB subgraphs into passages to narrow the gap between KB schemas and questions, which enables our model to benefit from recent advances in multilingual pre-trained language models (MPLMs) and cross-lingual machine reading comprehension (xMRC).

item.title: Knowledge-infused Contrastive Learning for Urban Imagery-based Socioeconomic Prediction
item.description: To address such issues, in this paper, we propose a Knowledge-infused Contrastive Learning (KnowCL) model for urban imagery-based socioeconomic prediction.

item.title: Partial Label Learning for Emotion Recognition from EEG
item.description: However, PLL methods have not yet been adopted for EEG representation learning or implemented for emotion recognition tasks.

item.title: TBFormer: Two-Branch Transformer for Image Forgery Localization
item.description: In this paper, we propose a Transformer-style network with two feature extraction branches for image forgery localization, and it is named as Two-Branch Transformer (TBFormer).

item.title: HADES: Homologous Automated Document Exploration and Summarization
item.description: This paper introduces HADES, a novel tool for automatic comparative documents with similar structures.

item.title: Jointly Optimizing Translations and Speech Timing to Improve Isochrony in Automatic Dubbing
item.description: Automatic dubbing (AD) is the task of translating the original speech in a video into target language speech.

item.title: Simulation of robot swarms for learning communication-aware coordination
item.description: These methods learn a controller by observing demonstrations of an expert, such as the behaviour of a centralised omniscient controller, which can perceive the entire environment, including the state and observations of all agents.

item.title: A parameter-free graph reduction for spectral clustering and SpectralNet
item.description: We introduce a graph reduction method that does not require any parameters.

item.title: The Effect of Points Dispersion on the $k$-nn Search in Random Projection Forests
item.description: $k$-nn search in an rpForest is influenced by two factors: 1) the dispersion of points along the random direction and 2) the number of rpTrees in the rpForest.

item.title: A Unified Framework for Soft Threshold Pruning
item.description: In this work, we reformulate soft threshold pruning as an implicit optimization problem solved using the Iterative Shrinkage-Thresholding Algorithm (ISTA), a classic method from the fields of sparse recovery and compressed sensing.

item.title: Fair Attribute Completion on Graph with Missing Attributes
item.description: Tackling unfairness in graph learning models is a challenging task, as the unfairness issues on graphs involve both attributes and topological structures.
